---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";

const snapshot = [
  { label: "Industry", value: "Fintech / Enterprise Platform" },
  { label: "Role", value: "UX Design Consultant" },
  { label: "Scope", value: "Global platform, cross-market servicing workflows" },
  { label: "Focus", value: "Usability, workflow clarity, system consistency" },
];

const decisions = [
  {
    title: "Workflow-first design",
    text: "We prioritized end-to-end servicing workflows over isolated screens, ensuring users could complete tasks efficiently across the system.",
  },
  {
    title: "Consistency through shared patterns",
    text: "We introduced consistent interaction patterns and design standards to reduce cognitive load and improve usability across regions.",
  },
  {
    title: "Localization with structural integrity",
    text: "We balanced global consistency with local market needs, ensuring the platform could scale without fragmentation.",
  },
];

const outcomes = [
  "Improved usability and reduced friction across complex servicing workflows.",
  "Increased consistency across platform experiences and interaction patterns.",
  "Strengthened foundation for scalable product development across global markets.",
  "Enabled clearer alignment between design, product, and engineering teams.",
];
---

<MainLayout title="Global Servicing Platform | Jorge Obando">
  <section class="case-study-page">

    <!-- HERO -->
    <section class="hero">
      <p class="eyebrow">American Express</p>
      <h1>Global Servicing Platform</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Improving a large-scale enterprise platform by simplifying workflows,
        strengthening UX foundations, and creating a more consistent and scalable system.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- SNAPSHOT -->
    <section class="snapshot-grid">
      {snapshot.map((item) => (
        <article class="snapshot-card">
          <p class="snapshot-label">{item.label}</p>
          <p class="snapshot-value">{item.value}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </section>

    <!-- SITUATION -->
    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>The situation</h2>
      <p>
        The platform supported complex servicing operations across multiple regions,
        but experiences were fragmented. Inconsistent interaction patterns and
        disconnected workflows created inefficiencies and increased cognitive load
        for users.
      </p>
      <p>
        As the platform expanded globally, these inconsistencies made it harder to
        maintain quality, scale effectively, and ensure a cohesive user experience.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- CHALLENGE -->
    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>The challenge</h2>
      <p>
        The challenge was to improve usability and consistency across a large,
        distributed system while supporting diverse workflows across regions and
        user types.
      </p>
      <p>
        This required aligning design patterns, simplifying workflows, and creating
        a stronger UX foundation that could scale without introducing additional
        complexity.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ROLE -->
    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>My role</h2>
      <p>
        As a UX Design Consultant, I worked across product, engineering, and design
        teams to improve the overall experience of the platform. I contributed to
        both strategic direction and execution, helping define patterns, workflows,
        and interaction models.
      </p>
      <p>
        My focus was on reducing fragmentation and improving how the system worked
        as a whole, rather than optimizing individual screens in isolation.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- HOW I OPERATED -->
    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>How I operated</h2>
      <div class="cards-grid two-up">

        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>Identified system-level issues</h3>
          <p>
            We analyzed workflows across the platform to identify inconsistencies,
            redundancies, and friction points.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>Established UX foundations</h3>
          <p>
            We introduced shared patterns and principles that improved consistency
            and usability across the system.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>Aligned teams</h3>
          <p>
            I worked with cross-functional teams to ensure design decisions were
            understood, implemented, and consistent across products.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>Improved execution quality</h3>
          <p>
            We strengthened the connection between design and engineering, reducing
            ambiguity and improving delivery outcomes.
          </p>
        </article>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- DECISIONS -->
    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Key decisions</h2>
      <div class="cards-grid one-up">
        {decisions.map((item) => (
          <article class="info-card">
            <h3>{item.title}</h3>
            <p>{item.text}</p>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- OUTCOMES -->
    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Outcomes</h2>
      <div class="outcomes-card">
        <ul>
          {outcomes.map((item) => (
            <li>{item}</li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- REFLECTION -->
    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Reflection</h2>
      <p>
        This work reinforced the importance of strong UX foundations in enterprise
        systems. Improving consistency and workflow clarity at the system level
        creates lasting impact—far beyond individual feature improvements.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- NEXT -->
    <section class="content-section next-step">
      <h2>Next case study</h2>
      <p>
        Return to <a href="/case-studies">all case studies</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

  </section>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .case-study-page {
    padding: 2.5rem 0 5rem;
  }

  .hero {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #a33a3a;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 4vw, 4.15rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }

  .lead {
    margin-top: 1.2rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: #555;
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .snapshot-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .snapshot-card,
  .info-card,
  .outcomes-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--divider);
    border-radius: 16px;
    background: #fff;
  }

  .snapshot-card {
    padding: 1.2rem;
  }

  .snapshot-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #777;
  }

  .snapshot-value {
    margin-top: 0.4rem;
  }

  .content-section {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--divider);
  }

  .cards-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .cards-grid.two-up {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
  }

  .info-card {
    padding: 1.4rem;
  }

  .outcomes-card {
    padding: 1.4rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .snapshot-grid,
    .cards-grid.two-up {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>